# Lodestar graph-freshness — union merge for generated graphs.
#
# `/lodestar-freshness` appends these lines to the workspace `.gitattributes`
# (committed) so two branches that both rebuilt a graph merge cleanly instead of
# conflicting on the generated JSON/report. The named driver is registered
# per-clone (not committed — it can't be):
#
#   git config merge.graphify-union.name   "graphify union merge for graph.json"
#   git config merge.graphify-union.driver "graphify merge-driver %O %A %B"
#
# If the driver isn't registered in a given clone (teammate/CI without graphify),
# git falls back to its normal 3-way merge — nothing breaks, you may just get an
# ordinary conflict on graph.json that a rebuild resolves.

docs/*/architecture/graph.json        merge=graphify-union
docs/*/architecture/GRAPH_REPORT.md   merge=graphify-union
